   "source": [
    "{\n",
    " \"cells\": [\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"# Legal Search Assistant\\n\",\"**NLP Project 36 of 100** — Retrieve relevant legal/contract passages by question using semantic search.\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"import subprocess, sys, importlib\\nfor pkg in ['pandas','numpy','sentence-transformers','scikit-learn']:\\n    try: importlib.import_module(pkg.replace('-','_'))\\n    except ImportError: subprocess.check_call([sys.executable,'-m','pip','install','-q',pkg])\\nprint('Ready.')\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"import numpy as np, pandas as pd\\nfrom sentence_transformers import SentenceTransformer\\nfrom sklearn.metrics.pairwise import cosine_similarity\\nprint('Loaded.')\\nmodel = SentenceTransformer('all-MiniLM-L6-v2')\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"# Synthetic legal passages\\npassages = [\\n    'The tenant shall pay rent on the first day of each month. Late fees of 5% apply after the 5th.',\\n    'Either party may terminate this agreement with 30 days written notice.',\\n    'The landlord is responsible for all structural repairs and maintenance of common areas.',\\n    'The tenant shall not sublease without prior written consent of the landlord.',\\n    'Security deposit of one month rent is required and refundable within 30 days of lease end.',\\n    'The tenant is liable for damages beyond normal wear and tear.',\\n    'This agreement shall be governed by the laws of the State of California.',\\n    'Force majeure events excuse performance for the duration of the event.',\\n    'Confidential information shall not be disclosed to third parties without consent.',\\n    'Arbitration shall be the exclusive method for resolving disputes under this agreement.',\\n]\\n\\npassage_embeddings = model.encode(passages)\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"def search(query, top_k=3):\\n    q_emb = model.encode([query])\\n    sims = cosine_similarity(q_emb, passage_embeddings)[0]\\n    top_idx = sims.argsort()[-top_k:][::-1]\\n    results = []\\n    for i in top_idx:\\n        results.append({'passage': passages[i], 'score': round(sims[i], 3)})\\n    return results\\n\\nqueries = ['When is rent due?', 'How to end the lease early?', 'Who handles repairs?', 'What about disputes?']\\nfor q in queries:\\n    print(f'\\\\nQ: {q}')\\n    for r in search(q, top_k=2):\\n        print(f'  [{r[\\\"score\\\"]}] {r[\\\"passage\\\"][:80]}')\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"## Summary\\n\",\"- **Semantic search finds relevant legal passages** even with natural language queries.\\n\",\"- **Sentence embeddings handle paraphrasing** better than keyword search.\\n\",\"- **For production, use hybrid search** (BM25 + dense) with citation tracking.\"]}\n",
    " ],\n",
